 not guilty and was released on a $75,000 bond.
In 2017, before joining MoviePass, Itum created Kaleidoscope Productions LL=
C and borrowed money from two individuals to put on the party during the Ap=
ril music festival in Indio, east of Los Angeles, according to the indictme=
nt. In November 2017, he became an executive at MoviePass, which had been a=
cquired by Helios & Matheson Analytics a few months earlier.=C2=A0
