<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9v=
enktbWVkaWEtY2VvLWNhcmxvcy13YXRzb24tYXJyZXN0ZWQtYWZ0ZXItYS1mb3JtZXItZXhlY3V=
0aXZlLXBsZWFkcy1ndWlsdHktdG8tZnJhdWQtMzU1ZTlmODk_bW9kPWhwX2xlYWRfcG9zMw/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4a479bb8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> this was inevitable</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ozy Media Chief Executive Carlos Watson was ar=
rested Thursday morning after a former executive with whom he founded the e=
mbattled startup pleaded guilty to fraud charges in a secretive federal cou=
rt proceeding.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Watson was taken into custody and is expec=
ted to be arraigned in a Brooklyn, N.Y., federal court on charges of conspi=
ring to commit securities fraud and conspiring to commit wire fraud, accord=
ing to a law-enforcement official. Ozy came under federal scrutiny for its =
business practices after the New York Times reported in 2021 that its then-=
chief operating officer, Samir Rao, impersonated an executive of Alphabet I=
nc.=E2=80=99s YouTube during a fundraising call with Goldman Sachs Group In=
c.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe are really disappointed,=E2=80=9D =
Lanny Breuer, Mr. Watson=E2=80=99s lawyer, said of his client=E2=80=99s arr=
est. =E2=80=9CWe have been acting in good faith and believe we had a constr=
uctive dialogue with the government and are shocked by the actions this mor=
ning.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Rao pleaded guilty Tuesday in Brooklyn fed=
eral court to fraud and identity theft charges, under a court-approved John=
 Doe pseudonym. He admitted to a U.S. magistrate judge that between 2018 an=
d 2021 he made misleading statements to investors and inflated the company=
=E2=80=99s financial performance. He also said he falsely used the identity=
 of another person without the authority to do so between February 2020 and=
 February 2021.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMjcvaW1wb3N0b3JzLW9uLXRoZS1kdWUtZGlsaWdlbmNlLWNhbGw_=
Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIyMzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5=
ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjIzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB64e133cd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked in 2021</a> about the time that =
Rao impersonated a YouTube executive on a due diligence call with Goldman. =
=E2=80=9COrdinarily if I were telling you this story,=E2=80=9D I wrote,=C2=
=A0=E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99d be quoting from a federal criminal complaint, or at=
 least a Securities and Exchange Commission enforcement action, but nope ev=
erything is fine!=E2=80=9D Well, now there is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3Y=
vdXNhby1lZG55L3ByL296eS1tZWRpYS1hbmQtaXRzLWZvdW5kZXItY2FybG9zLXdhdHNvbi1pbm=
RpY3RlZC15ZWFycy1sb25nLW11bHRpLW1pbGxpb24tZG9sbGFyLWZyYXVk/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB04ab2f30" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;"> a federal criminal case</a>, and also an <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0zNw/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBf7b93a48" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">SEC enforcement action</a>.=C2=A0From the <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1lZG55L3ByL296eS1tZWRpYS1hbmQtaXRzLWZvdW5kZXItY2F=
ybG9zLXdhdHNvbi1pbmRpY3RlZC15ZWFycy1sb25nLW11bHRpLW1pbGxpb24tZG9sbGFyLWZyYX=
Vk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC04ab2f30" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> prosecutors=E2=80=99 announc=
ement</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An indictment was unsealed this morning in fed=
eral court in Brooklyn charging OZY Media Inc. (Ozy), a media and entertain=
ment company headquartered in Mountain View, California, and its founder an=
d Chief Executive Officer, Carlos Watson, with conspiracy to commit securit=
ies fraud and conspiracy to commit wire fraud in connection with a scheme t=
o defraud Ozy=E2=80=99s investors and lenders by making material misreprese=
ntations about Ozy=E2=80=99s financial and business assets. =C2=A0Watson is=
 also charged with aggravated identity theft for his role in the impersonat=
ion of multiple media company executives in communications with Ozy=E2=80=
=99s lenders and prospective investors in furtherance of the fraud schemes.=
=C2=A0 =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CAs alleged, Carlos Watson is a con ma=
n whose business strategy was based on outright deceit and fraud =E2=80=93 =
he ran Ozy as a criminal organization rather than as a reputable media comp=
any,=E2=80=9D stated United States Attorney Peace. =C2=A0=E2=80=9CInvestmen=
t fraud undermines confidence in our nation=E2=80=99s markets and investors=
 and makes it harder for honest businesses to compete. =C2=A0Our Office and=
 the Department of Justice have made it clear that prosecuting corporations=
 and their corrupt executives who flagrantly violate the law are top priori=
ties.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CAs the indictment today alleges, Wats=
on repeatedly attempted to entice both investors and lenders through a seri=
es of deliberate deceptions and fabrications. =C2=A0The FBI and our partner=
s in law enforcement will hold any individual willing to defraud investors =
and financial institutions accountable in the criminal justice system,=E2=
=80=9D stated Assistant Director-in-Charge Driscoll.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CHis role in the impersonation of mult=
iple media company executives=E2=80=9D!? Multiple? What? Here=E2=80=99s the=
 other one:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In December 2019, Watson and his c=
o-conspirators attempted to induce a bank to lend Ozy money based on misrep=
resentations and omissions about Ozy=E2=80=99s business. =C2=A0Watson and h=
is co-conspirators sought to secure the loan with anticipated revenues from=
 a second season of an Ozy television show. =C2=A0However, the contract bet=
ween Ozy and the show=E2=80=99s cable network for the second season of the =
show was still under negotiation. =C2=A0To induce the bank to make the loan=
 sooner, Watson directed Ozy=E2=80=99s then-Chief Financial Officer (CFO) t=
o send the bank a fake signed contract between Ozy and the cable network pu=
rporting to be for the second season. =C2=A0When the then-CFO refused, Rao,=
 with Watson=E2=80=99s approval, sent the fake contract =E2=80=94 which con=
tained terms favorable to Ozy and a forged signature =E2=80=94 to the bank,=
 copying the then-CFO. =C2=A0Later that day, the then-CFO emailed Watson an=
d Rao to say that she was resigning effective immediately. =C2=A0She explai=
ned, =E2=80=9Cthis . . . is illegal. =C2=A0This is fraud. =C2=A0This is for=
ging someone=E2=80=99s signature with the intent of getting an advance from=
 a publicly traded bank.=E2=80=9D =C2=A0She continued, =E2=80=9CTo be cryst=
al clear, what you see as a measured risk =E2=80=94 I see as a felony.=E2=
=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean, yes, but I am a little confused that s=
he sent that email in 2019 and the charges are only coming in 2023? Like if=
 you send that email to your boss on the way out the door, isn=E2=80=99t yo=
ur next stop at the SEC to get a whistleblower deal? Also here is this abou=
t the YouTube call:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On or about February 2, 2021, Rao =
had a call with employees of the financial institution during which he impe=
rsonated a media executive from the online video service using a voice alte=
ration application that he downloaded onto his cellular telephone to mask h=
is voice during the call. =C2=A0During the call, Watson was in the same roo=
m as Rao, and texted Rao instructions about what to say and what not to say=
 on the call. =C2=A0Shortly after the call, one of the employees of the fin=
ancial institution contacted the actual media executive of the online video=
 service, who confirmed that he had not been on the call and that the onlin=
e video service had no role in the production of The Carlos Watson Show. =
=C2=A0When members of the financial institution later spoke with Watson, he=
 falsely claimed that Rao had acted alone and as a result of a mental break=
down.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The indictment <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3Yvd=
XNhby1lZG55L3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvZmlsZS8xNTY5NjMxL2Rvd25sb2Fk/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cBa49aa5bd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> describes the text messages</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Throughout the call, the defendant=
 CARLOS WATSON sent a series of text messages to Rao, which included instru=
ctions of what to say and not say. For example, at approximately 11:19 a.m.=
 (EST), WATSON texted Rao, 'i am a big fan of Carlos, Samir and the show." =
At approximately 11:21 a.m. (EST), WATSON texted Rao, "Use the right pronou=
ns ... You are NOT OZY." At approximately 11:26 a.m. (EST), after Rao had r=
epeatedly used the first name of one of the employees of Financial Institut=
ion 1 who was on the call, WATSON texted Rao, "Stop using her name."</p></b=
lockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess Rao kept saying =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=9D w=
hen he meant =E2=80=9COzy=E2=80=9D? Which an actual YouTube executive would=
 not say? And he kept addressing the Goldman employee by name, because he i=
s a salesperson (and a former Goldman employee himself), but of course an a=
ctual YouTube executive hopping on a random diligence call probably wouldn=
=E2=80=99t even know her name? Not so easy to impersonate people, is it?</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those are just the=C2=A0<em>impersonation=C2=
=A0</em>charges, but there are various more normal sorts of alleged fraud t=
oo. Watson <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3064023=
1.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMy9jb2=
1wLXByMjAyMy0zNy5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB41697ebe" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> allegedly=
 told a broker</a> =E2=80=9Cthat a well-known hedge fund manager =E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0had already committed a $5 million investment=E2=80=9D to Ozy=E2=80=
=99s Series C round; the manager was actually in the round but for just und=
er $1 million. A pitch deck allegedly =E2=80=9Cstated that Ozy=E2=80=99s 20=
18 revenue was $22 million when, in fact, it was about $10 million, and tha=
t certain well-known investors were =E2=80=98leading=E2=80=99 the Series C =
round, when they were not.=E2=80=9D In the Series D round, Watson and Rao a=
llegedly told the broker =E2=80=9Cthat a television star=E2=80=99s company =
and a famous live entertainment company would be leading the round,=E2=80=
=9D when they were not investors at all.=C2=A0In the pitch to Goldman, they=
 sent a deck that allegedly =E2=80=9Cinflated Ozy=E2=80=99s earnings before=
 interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization (=E2=80=98EBITDA=E2=80=99)=
 numbers by over 70% for 2018 and approximately 80% for 2019.=E2=80=9D=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing that we <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMDYvZG9nZWNvaW4taXMtdXAtYmVjYXVzZS1pd=
C1zLWZ1bm55P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMjMyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRt=
X3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIyMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHV=
mZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBed8fca87" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talk about</a>=C2=A0someti=
mes=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30640231.=
258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDIt=
MjYvc3RhcnR1cHMtc29tZXRpbWVzLXN0cmV0Y2gtdGhlLXRydXRoP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMjMyM19=
NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZX=
JtPTIzMDIyMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB89221=
fdb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">around here</a> is that there is probably a certain leeway for=
 private companies to, uh, exaggerate slightly in their fundraising pitches=
. Not legal advice or anything! But the investors kind of expect it: They=
=C2=A0<em>want=C2=A0</em>visionary, envelope-pushing, see-the-world-not-as-=
it-is-but-as-it-could-be founders, so they are willing to tolerate some fou=
nders who are not constrained by reality, and to write off fraud losses as =
=E2=80=9Cwell, lots of startups fail.=E2=80=9D Plus the audience for startu=
p pitches is smaller than that for public companies, and the investors don=
=E2=80=99t want to be embarrassed: If you got hoodwinked by a startup, it d=
oesn=E2=80=99t really do much for your reputation to go around complaining =
about it loudly.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is Ozy the first private company to send an in=
vestor a pitch deck that inflated its Ebitda by 70% or 80%? Probably not, n=
o. But in recent years there does seem to have been a bit of a crackdown on=
 private-company securities fraud. Some of that is due to <a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30640231.258438/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmx=
vb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDEtMDQvc2xheWluZy10aGUtYmxvb2=
QtdW5pY29ybj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMjIzMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0b=
V9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAyMjMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1=
ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB334ad31b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  the influence of Theranos<=
/a>, I think, and some of it is just that private markets are bigger and mo=
re important than they used to be. =E2=80=9CPrivate markets are the new pub=
lic markets,=E2=80=9D I sometimes say, and if you can raise billions of dol=
lars from big institutions in private markets then you probably will get tr=
eated more like a public company.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also the main thing is probably just that if y=
ou do a fraud that is so egregious and hilarious that it becomes national n=
ews, you will get in trouble. If you are marking up your Ebitda a bit in pi=
tches to private investors, prosecutors and the SEC might never hear about =
it, but if you are doing multiple elaborate impersonations to raise money y=
ou are eventually going to attract attention.</p>
